  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_3' aria-label=\" Vijay Krishnaswami @ Krishnaswami Vijayakumar versus The Deputy Director of Income Tax (Investigation) pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('3','2025','2025_8_2199_2226','2025INSC1048'); ><font size='4'> <strong>VIJAY KRISHNASWAMI @ KRISHNASWAMI VIJAYAKUMAR<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>THE DEPUTY DIRECTOR OF INCOME TAX (INVESTIGATION) </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 8 S.C.R. 2199</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 1048</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010008502025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : J.K. MAHESHWARI<sup style=\"color: #268e97;font-size: 22px;top: 0;\" class=\"tooltip-sup\" data-tooltip=\"Author\">*</sup></strong><br> Issue for Consideration Whether continuation of the prosecution initiated by the revenue u/s.276C(1), Income Tax Act, 1961 against the appellant after passing an order by the Settlement Commission, would amount to abuse of process of Court; of the present case, the High Court was justified to dismiss the quashing petition filed by the appellant, and if not, what relief can be granted. Headnotes&dagger; Income Tax Act, 1961 &ndash; ss.276C(1), 245H(1) proviso to, 245D(4), 245I &ndash; Search conducted at the residence of the<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 28-08-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CRIMINAL APPEAL No. 3777/2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Appeal(s) allowed</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('3','2025','2025_8_2199_2226','2025INSC1048','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></i